refactor(explorations): show only exploration fields in 'Add from exploration' modals

Strip page-specific base inputs (name, parent IDs, role, level, donor, etc.)
from every 'Add from exploration' modal across the platform. The exploration
template now drives the entire record: every value, including parent links,
is derived from the dynamic fields configured by the form designer.

useExplorationForm now exposes three helpers used at save time:
- getValueBySource(sourceId): read the first field whose option source is
  the requested platform collection (governorates, regions, villages,
  permission_profiles...)
- getValueByType(fieldType): read the first field of a given input type
  (tel, password, email, url, number...)
- deriveDisplayName(fallback): pick a reasonable display name from a
  name-like text field, with sensible fallbacks

Page-level rewrites:
- Governorates: derives name from a name-like text field.
- Regions: derives name, requires a field sourced from 'governorates'
  for the parent govId.
- Schools: derives name, requires a field sourced from 'villages'
  for the parent villageId; defaults schoolLevel/donorName.
- Users / Student Management: derives displayName from name-like field,
  reads phone (tel), password (password) and optional email/photo from
  typed fields; permissionProfileId can come from a field sourced from
  'permission_profiles'.
- Curriculum: derives name and creates the empty 50-week plan.
- Teacher Students: derives studentName and reads age from a number field.

Villages keeps a single page-specific block (سجل المهتدين والمسلمين القدامى)
on top of the exploration fields per the requirement that legacy fields
elsewhere disappear. The page was also refactored onto the shared
useExplorationForm hook + ExplorationFormSection component for parity
with the rest of the platform.

When the chosen template is missing a required parent source or a
recognizable name field, the modal surfaces a clear Arabic error
instead of saving an inconsistent record.
